SIMPLE: ampule
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: ampule
<hw>ampule</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>a small glass bottle
which has been or can be sealed hermetically by application of flame to
a narrow opening at the top.</def> <note>aAn ampule usually has a narrow
constriction near the top which can be scored and easily broken to open
the ampule. Once opened, they cannot be hermetically re-sealed; thus the
quantity contained is usually that which is to be used at once or within
a short time. The contents are often sealed under vacuum to retard
degradation by air.</note>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> phial, vial, ampoule</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>an ampule, or vial resembling an ampule, which
contains a drug.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ampulla</ent>⟦br⟧
\'d8
